# auto-goal

## Context Profile

Load core workspace policy only. Goal state is runtime state, not project context.

## Contract

- `status`: use the native goal status tool when available and report objective, status, budget, and next required step.
- `"<objective>" [--budget N]`: check for an active goal before creating one; use a token budget only when explicitly supplied.
- `complete`: mark complete only when the objective is achieved and no required work remains.
- `blocked`: mark blocked only after the same condition recurs for at least three consecutive goal turns.
- `clear`, `pause`, `resume`: use the matching runtime slash command if supported.
- Antigravity has no Codex goal persistence contract. Never write goal state to `.autopus`; explain the limitation and provide the matching Codex `/goal` fallback when native tools are absent.
